<ns1516:section xmlns:ns1516="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.tecnologies.java.j2se.java2D.drawingShapes.drawingShapes">
    
    <ns1517:title xmlns:ns1517="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Drawing Shapes</ns1517:title>

<ns1518:para xmlns:ns1518="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Java 2D supplies a general <ns1519:emphasis xmlns:ns1519="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="verb">Shape</ns1519:emphasis> interface which is implemented by
a collection of standard shapes like lines, rectangles, ellipses, arcs, ...</ns1518:para>

<ns1520:para xmlns:ns1520="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The outline of 2-dimensional shapes is drawn with the current stroke of the
graphics context. One thus first creates a <ns1521:emphasis xmlns:ns1521="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="verb">BasicStroke</ns1521:emphasis> object, sets
the current stroke of the graphics context via the <ns1522:emphasis xmlns:ns1522="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="verb">setStroke(stroke)</ns1522:emphasis>
method, creates a specific <ns1523:emphasis xmlns:ns1523="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="verb">Shape</ns1523:emphasis> object and draws it via the 
<ns1524:emphasis xmlns:ns1524="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="verb">draw(shape)</ns1524:emphasis> service of the graphics context.
</ns1520:para>
<ns1525:para xmlns:ns1525="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The standard shapes supplied with Java 2D come in low and high-precision 
versions. For example, <ns1526:emphasis xmlns:ns1526="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="verb">Rectangle2D</ns1526:emphasis> is an abstract base class with
nested concrete subclasses <ns1527:emphasis xmlns:ns1527="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="verb">Rectangle2d.Double</ns1527:emphasis> and 
<ns1528:emphasis xmlns:ns1528="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="verb">Rectangle2D.Float</ns1528:emphasis> (these are static nested classes, see section
on Static Nested Classes).</ns1525:para>

<ns1529:para xmlns:ns1529="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">All shapes implement the <ns1530:emphasis xmlns:ns1530="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" role="verb">Shape</ns1530:emphasis> interface which contains methods for 
checking for inclusion, checking for shape bounds, checking for intersection
and for obtaining a path iterator for the shape.</ns1529:para>

